comment:
The thing is that Depp HASS NOT BEEN fired from the Caribbean any more than Heard has been fired from Aquaman. If you chase up the actual interviews of "Disney confirming", Disney hasn't confirmed anything. 

The writer was asked, "is it POSSIBLE  that JD isn't returning.." He says "it's possible, I am not sure if I am returning to it, we're waiting for a decision" or something to that effect. POSSIBLE, NOT confirmed. He wasn't even in the position of confirming a thing on behalf of Disney.

When the Disney executive was asked the same thing, he avoided the question and said JD has had great success in Pirates, and that will be his legacy, but he did not, AT ALL confirm that he'd been fired. In the next sentence, he confirms "the reboot" is going ahead WITH A NEW WRITING TEAM, in other words, the previously mentioned writer was fired or benched, not Depp. 

Next, they ran a story in which the NEW WRITING TEAM was fired, again, not Depp.

Now... If this was official, it would be difficult for Depp to prove Amber has in any way caused a slump in his income, which she has, but losing Pirates seems like the biggest problem she's created for him... But no. Disney hasn't confirmed a thing, any more than WB would do. However, it was probably best for Disney to also not confirm that they haven't fired Depp.
